&lt;p&gt;The post &lt;a href="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/news/idc-how-emea-cios-can-jumpstart-ai-rollouts/"&gt;IDC: How EMEA CIOs can jumpstart AI rollouts&lt;/a&gt; appeared first on &lt;a href="https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com"&gt;AI News&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.artificialintelligence-news.com/?p=113184</guid><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 14:02:45 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: AI tutors for Python, Ruby, and JavaScript powered by my personal notes</title><link>https://github.com/JoeCardoso13/brush-up-backend</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Live demos (also linked at the top of the repo):&lt;p&gt;- &lt;a href="https://joecardoso.dev/brush-up-py" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://joecardoso.dev/brush-up-py&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;- &lt;a href="https://joecardoso.dev/brush-up-rb" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://joecardoso.dev/brush-up-rb&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;- &lt;a href="https://joecardoso.dev/brush-up-js" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://joecardoso.dev/brush-up-js&lt;/a&gt;&lt;p&gt;The retrieval engine, although simple, sparks some interesting ideas, e.g.: what if instead of Zettelkasten notes you had summaries of codebase sections, and instead of [[wikilinks]] you had signposts to architectural dependencies? Graph traversal over a codebase map could be a way to help agents navigate large repos while keeping context window usage deliberate and bounded.&lt;/p&gt;
